TITLE: Initializing Basic Silex Application with Route Handler
DESCRIPTION: Basic example showing how to set up a Silex application with autoloader, define a GET route with a name parameter, and run the application. The route handler returns an escaped greeting using the provided name parameter.
SOURCE: https://github.com/silexphp/Silex/blob/master/doc/intro.rst#2025-04-15_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

// web/index.php
require_once __DIR__.'/../vendor/autoload.php';

$app = new Silex\Application();

$app->get('/hello/{name}', function ($name) use ($app) {
    return 'Hello '.$app->escape($name);
});

$app->run();
```

