TITLE: Parsing JSON Request Body in Silex Middleware
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create a before middleware in Silex that parses the JSON request body when the Content-Type header indicates JSON content. It decodes the JSON and replaces the request data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/silexphp/Silex/blob/master/doc/cookbook/json_request_body.rst#2025-04-15_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
use Symfony\Component\HttpFoundation\Request;
use Symfony\Component\HttpFoundation\ParameterBag;

$app->before(function (Request $request) {
    if (0 === strpos($request->headers->get('Content-Type'), 'application/json')) {
        $data = json_decode($request->getContent(), true);
        $request->request->replace(is_array($data) ? $data : array());
    }
});
```

