TITLE: Creating a Factory Function for Multiple Monolog Loggers in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This code creates a factory function that generates new Monolog logger instances with different channel names but the same handler. It then uses a loop to create loggers for 'auth', 'payments', and 'stats' channels.
SOURCE: https://github.com/silexphp/Silex/blob/master/doc/cookbook/multiple_loggers.rst#2025-04-15_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
$app['monolog.factory'] = $app->protect(function ($name) use ($app) {
    $log = new $app['monolog.logger.class']($name);
    $log->pushHandler($app['monolog.handler']);

